{"tid":1150891,"cid":23,"subCid":0,"title":"之前影香港幾咁壓迫個德國攝影師死咗","createTime":"2019-05-12T07:41:44.000Z","updateTime":"2019-05-12T13:10:58.000Z","uid":56118,"like":0,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":7,"replies":[{"pid":"4c2119603774d8b367d32b94255a2fb5027a3c10","tid":1150891,"uid":56118,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-12T07:41:44.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2019/apr/26/how-photographer-michael-wolf-captured-the-planets-teeming-city-life#img-3\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fartanddesign%2F2019%2Fapr%2F26%2Fhow-photographer-michael-wolf-captured-the-planets-teeming-city-life%23img-3&h=ee2a47b4&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nMichael Wolf, who has died suddenly, aged 64, was perhaps best known for his 2013-14 series, Architecture of Density, in which the facades of Hong Kong&rsquo;s massive tower blocks, each one housing thousands of people, appear as dramatic geometric abstractions of light and colour. Hong Kong&rsquo;s population density is around 6,987 people per square kilometre, and many of them live in tiny flats in these massive buildings. In Wolf&rsquo;s photographs, the people are invisible, but on closer inspection, their presence is evident everywhere &ndash; in the coloured curtains, the laundry hanging out to dry, the sheets that drape on scaffolding."},{"pid":"53654f1a09ea9c5f78f523593ddc3ed3e59feef2","tid":1150891,"uid":50196,"like":13,"dislike":1,"score":12,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-12T07:49:00.000Z","msg":"岩岩出冊？"},{"pid":"8fce7aba513b0401a088e16e755174f527b4606e","tid":1150891,"uid":38218,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-12T07:49:42.000Z","msg":"Michael Wolf死左<br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/1125832\" target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/1125832</a>"},{"pid":"19f71c4efd9fe433b9f3948e7de9365fabe8f65b","tid":1150891,"uid":71341,"like":0,"dislike":12,"score":-12,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05